Coach Ayanda Dlamini of AmaZulu during the AmaZulu press conference at the Prime HPI at Moses Mabhida Stadium in Durban on 9 September 2020 JOHANNESBURG - AmaZulu has appointed Ayanda Dlamini as permanent head coach on a three-year contract. The former Usuthu striker was made interim coach at the beginning of the year when the club suspended then-coach Jozef Vukusic who has since been fired. Dlamini has been rewarded for a sterling job he did after saving AmaZulu from relegation.